Command and Q - quit
Command and M - minimise window
Command and S - save screenshot
Command and - (minus sign) - reduce scale (both x and y)
Command and = (equal sign) - reduce scale (both x and y)
Command and 0 - go back to default scale and origin
Command and 9 - equalise the scale x and scale y
Command and 8 - go back to origin
Command and Backspace - remove function
Command and N - add a new function
Enter - make function visible/invisible
up/down arrow - switch from functions
left/right arrow - move cursor in function editor
mouse left and drag - move origin
mouse right and drag - adjust scale x and y according to movement
Shift and middle mouse scroll - scale x and y
